<!--
    Android 13+ themed-icon (Material You) monochrome layer, referenced
    by the <monochrome> element in mipmap-anydpi-v26/ic_launcher{,_round}.xml.
    The launcher treats opaque pixels as a mask and tints them with the
    wallpaper accent. Same glyph + transform as ic_stat_cardigan.xml
    (traced from public/icon-mono.svg, ~18% built-in safe margin, which
    keeps the glyph inside the adaptive-icon safe zone without an extra
    inset wrapper).

    ⚠️ CI's icon-generation step (npx @capacitor/assets generate, Android
    mode) rewrites the two adaptive-icon XMLs from a template WITHOUT a
    monochrome slot. scripts/apply-android-config.sh re-inserts the
    element after that step (wired in android-build.yml); keep both in
    sync. (Phrasing here avoids a literal double hyphen, which is illegal
    inside XML comments.)
-->
